main event: A star-shaped object was observed by the pilot of United Airlines Flight #255 over Stockton, California at an altitude of approximately 9,000 feet.
interesting points: The object appeared to be about 1/50 the diameter of the sun's length.
The object was heading north at a very high rate of speed.
The object disappeared by blinking out for one minute.
The pilot of United Airlines Flight #255 first noticed the object over Santa Barbara.
Other pilots in the area also reported seeing the same object.
